<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <tal:branch-link define="branch context">
    <metal:branch-link use-macro="context/@@+macros/branch-heading-link"/>
  </tal:branch-link>
  <h1>Register merge proposal</h1>

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">
  </div>

</div><tal:comment condition="nothing"><!-- end main slot --></tal:comment>

<metal:block fill-slot="help">

  <p>
    The purpose of a branch merge proposal is to indicate that one
    branch is intending to be merged back into another branch.
  </p>

  <p>
    The target branch is where the code will eventually be merged
    into.
  </p>

  <p>
    The dependent branch allows you to indicate that the branch
    <em><tal:branch-name replace="context/displayname"/></em>
    was branched of a different branch than the target branch.
  </p>


</metal:block><tal:comment condition="nothing"><!-- end help slot --></tal:comment>

</body>
</html>
<!-- 1-0 done -->
